  "bead": {
    "id": "ddx-34ea2a74",
    "title": "agent: normalize readiness refinable aliases and diagnose schema drift",
    "description": "PROBLEM\nDuring the 2026-06-14 dogfood worker restart, readiness for ddx-824079ce returned classification=\"refinable\" after useful inspection, but DDx rejected it with `unknown classification \"refinable\": expected one of ready, needs_refine, needs_split, operator_required, system_unready` and then fail-opened with `readiness check unavailable`. A similar helix readiness pass returned executable prose but surfaced as `system_unready`. DDx/FIZ must make provider/schema drift actionable and must not disguise common near-miss readiness output as project unreadiness.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\ncli/internal/agent/readiness_classification.go:126-140 normalizes several aliases, including actionable_but_rewritten, rewritten, and safely_refinable, but omits the plain `refinable` alias that providers naturally emit. cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:2751-2804 and :2830-2854 convert intake errors into `pre_claim_intake.system_unready` warnings with the generic suggested action `check the readiness route or harness configuration and retry`, losing whether the problem was an output-schema/normalization issue versus a real project readiness blocker.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Normalize `classification: \"refinable\"` to `needs_refine` in the readiness classifier.\n- Add regression coverage proving `refinable` does not become an unknown classification and is handled according to the existing warn/block quality mode.\n- Improve intake-error diagnostics so unknown readiness classifications are recorded as provider/schema drift with the raw classification and accepted enum set, not as generic system_unready project failure.\n- Preserve the existing fail-open behavior unless quality mode says to block; this bead is about correct classification and observability, not making readiness stricter.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not change the canonical readiness enum names.\n- Do not alter FIZ route selection.\n- Do not change the worker claim/lease policy beyond diagnostics for unknown readiness classification.",
    "acceptance": "1. `TestNormalizeReadinessClassificationRefinableAlias` proves `ClassifyReadinessWithMode(\"refinable\", ...)` normalizes to `needs_refine` rather than returning an unknown classification.\n2. `TestReadinessUnknownClassificationDiagnosticNamesSchemaDrift` proves an unknown readiness classification records a diagnostic that includes the raw classification and the accepted enum set, and does not describe the bead itself as system-unready without that schema-drift context.\n3. `TestPreClaimIntakeRefinableAliasFollowsNeedsRefinePolicy` proves the work/pre-claim path treats `classification: \"refinable\"` like `needs_refine` under existing warn/block quality modes.\n4. Existing readiness classification tests in `cli/internal/agent/readiness_schema_test.go` and work readiness tests continue to pass.\n5. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -run 'TestNormalizeReadinessClassificationRefinableAlias|TestReadinessUnknownClassificationDiagnosticNamesSchemaDrift|TestPreClaimIntakeRefinableAliasFollowsNeedsRefinePolicy' -count=1` passes.\\n6. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.",
    "parent": "ddx-9d1af129",
